\begin_layout Subsection
\paragraph_spacing double
Comparison of the Asset Allocation Weights
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing double
The differences in the efficient frontier performance in terms of returns
 and CVaR stems from the different asset allocations for each portfolio.
 In order to visualize the differences in the allocation of capital amongst
 the seven asset classes, we used a 3D-ribbon graph for each of the optimal
 efficient frontiers (mean-variance and mean-CVaR) in Figures 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:ribbon_Mean-Variance-Weights"

\end_inset

, 
